
// This Hyperlambda code snippet replaces all double spaces in the [.prompt] node's value with a single space. It uses the [strings.replace] slot to search for occurrences of double spaces and substitutes them with a single space, effectively normalizing the spacing within the text. The [set-value] slot updates the [.prompt] node with the modified string.
set-value:x:@.prompt
   strings.replace:x:@.prompt
      .:"  "
      .:" "
